      "analytePanel": "Delhi MAGICL 6000i assay menu (15 assays) captured from the analyzer Item Setup > Item Param screen (2026-07-24): TSH, FSH, 25-OH-VD, Vitamin B12, T3, T4, LH, Estradiol, CA125, PRL, AMH, CA19-9, beta-HCG, TPSA, Progesterone.",
      "source": "Delhi MAGICL 6000i, serial M022W0000396. Network + LIS settings captured from the analyzer System Setup screens (2026-07-24). Noble targets resolved and name-verified against the live catalog on 2026-07-24; the 9 numeric item-ids reused here were verified on the Karnal MAGICL against real eLab Assist HL7 traffic.",
      "mappingsSummary": { "total": 45, "mapped": 42, "unmapped": 3 },
      "_mappingNotes": [
        "Analyte key (instrumentCode) is the MAGICL numeric assay item-id carried in OBX-3 — NOT a mnemonic. It is also what the host query sends back as the ordered assay, so a wrong id means the analyzer either rejects the order (MA00F 'Assay Not Found') or runs the wrong assay.",
        "PROVENANCE: every one of the 45 menu items had its id read directly off THIS analyzer's Item Setup > Item Param screens (2026-07-24). Nothing here is inferred from another site. The preset originally borrowed 9 ids from the Karnal MAGICL capture as a stopgap; all 9 have since been confirmed on this instrument (TSH=18, T3=19, T4=20, FSH=24, LH=27, VitD=42, AMH=79, B12=139, tPSA=8), as have Ferritin=6, IgE=25 and CCP=157 — i.e. all 12 assays Karnal and Delhi share carry identical ids, so MAGICL item-ids are vendor-standard rather than per-site.",
        "The analyzer converts between its own 'Unit' and the 'LIS Unit' it transmits: T3 nmol/L->ng/mL, T4 nmol/L->ug/dL, FT4 pmol/L->ng/dL, Testosterone ng/mL->ng/dL. The unit recorded in each mapping below is the LIS Unit (what actually arrives), not the analyzer's internal unit.",
        "TWO ASSAYS RELY ON A SYNAPSE-SIDE CONVERSION (src/main/core/engine/units.ts, covered by npm run verify:units): FT3 arrives as pmol/L and is converted x0.651 to Noble's pg/mL; FT4 arrives as ng/dL and is converted x10 to Noble's ng/L. Both rules are keyed on the source AND target unit, so if the analyzer's LIS Unit is ever changed to match Noble directly the rule stops firing rather than double-converting. If you DO change either LIS Unit on the instrument, also update the unit recorded in the mapping below so the pair stays consistent.",
        "Every LIS target below was unit-verified against real Noble result rows (sampled testunit + values on 2026-07-24), not just name-matched. That check is what caught the FT3 and Rubella/CMV problems in _pendingMappings.",
        "Infectious-disease targets resolve to Noble's CLIA-method entries, which store exactly the analyzer's units: HBsAg -> HBSCL (IU/ml), HCV -> hcvcl (S/CO), HIV -> HIVCL (S/CO). NOT the CMIA/ELISA/Rapid variants of the same assays, and NOT MS065 (which stores unit 'TV'). LAB POLICY: these auto-release reactive results into Noble. If your SOP requires manual confirmation before a reactive HIV/HBsAg/HCV is filed, set those three rules to 'ignored' in Synapse > Mappings after applying the preset.",
        "fPSA targets test 126 (BI107) parameter 521 'Prostatic Specific Antigen-Free FPSA' — deliberately NOT parameter 520, which is the Free/Total RATIO (a derived quantity Noble calculates).",
        "Parameterized Noble tests write to the PARAMETER (lisParamId); TSH, T3, T4, VitD, TPO-Ab, CK-MB, CA15-3, HBsAg, HCV and HIV are standalone test-level rows (no param).",
        "HSV-I IgG: Noble labels the unit 'OD Ratio' where the analyzer sends 'S/CO'. Both are cutoff-index ratios on the same scale, and the repository never overwrites Noble's unit label, so this is a label difference only.",
        "OVERLAP WITH THE DELHI X3: the two menus now overlap on ~21 assays — Cortisol, C-Peptide, Ferritin, Folate, Insulin, NT-proBNP, CCP, TSH, T3, T4, FSH, LH, VitD, VitB12, PSA, IgE, Prolactin, Progesterone, beta-HCG, Testosterone and 17-OHP/AMH. Host query will offer the same ordered test to BOTH instruments, so a sample can be run twice and whichever finishes first fills the Noble cell (fill-blanks-only). Decide per assay which analyzer owns it and set the other instrument's rule to 'ignored'.",
        "SUSPECTED BUG IN THE X3 MAPPING (not fixed here — needs the X3's own LIS Unit screen to confirm): this preset's maglumi-x3 entry maps TESTO -> BI209 with unit ng/mL, but Noble stores Testosterone-Total in ng/dL (verified: 300/300 rows ng/dL, values 4.95-283). Those differ 100x. The MAGICL transmits ng/dL and is mapped accordingly. Check what the X3 actually sends before trusting its Testosterone results.",
        "Connection: the analyzer is the TCP CLIENT. Its LIS screen has Ethernet Port, Server IP 192.168.1.106, COM Port 8081 — so the Delhi Synapse host must hold 192.168.1.106 on the instrument LAN and listen as tcp-server on 8081. The analyzer itself is static 192.168.1.159/24, gateway 192.168.1.253. No analyzer IP is entered in Synapse.",
        "'Auto access tests' is ticked on the analyzer, i.e. host query is ON: enable Host Query in Synapse so it answers QRY^Q02 with QCK+DSR and ACKs each ORU^R01."
      ],
      "_pendingMappings": [
        { "instrumentCode": "144", "instrumentName": "CMV IgG", "lisTestId": 183, "lisTestCode": "MS029", "lisTestName": "CMV - IgG Antibody", "lisParamId": 874, "lisParamName": "Cytomegalovirus - IgG", "unit": "AU/mL", "_blockedBy": "DELIBERATELY UNMAPPED (lab decision, 2026-07-24). MEASURAND MISMATCH: the analyzer reports a qualitative S/CO cutoff ratio; Noble stores a quantitative AU/mL titre (verified 400/400 rows AU/mL). Not a scalar conversion, so no unit rule can fix it. Entered manually. Target details are kept here so it can be mapped later if a ratio-based Noble test is created (cf. HSV-I/II, which map to CP-series tests storing 'OD Ratio')." },
        { "instrumentCode": "145", "instrumentName": "Rubella IgG", "lisTestId": 211, "lisTestCode": "MS087", "lisTestName": "Rubella Virus - IgG Anti body", "lisParamId": 1082, "lisParamName": "Rubella virus - IgG", "unit": "AU/mL", "_blockedBy": "DELIBERATELY UNMAPPED (lab decision, 2026-07-24). Same S/CO-vs-AU/mL mismatch as CMV IgG (verified 400/400 rows AU/mL). Entered manually. NOTE the Delhi X3 preset already maps RUBELLA to this same MS087 with unit IU/mL — that mapping is unaffected by this decision and should still be re-checked." },
        { "instrumentCode": "146", "instrumentName": "Toxo IgG", "lisTestId": 221, "lisTestCode": "MS092", "lisTestName": "Toxoplasma gondii  - IgG Anti body", "lisParamId": 1103, "lisParamName": "Toxoplasma gondii - IgG", "unit": "AU/mL", "_blockedBy": "DELIBERATELY UNMAPPED (lab decision, 2026-07-24). Same S/CO-vs-AU/mL mismatch as CMV IgG (verified 300/300 rows AU/mL). Entered manually." }
      ],
